[30;1m214 | [0m[35m    auto node = m_pointerMap.lower_bound(ptr);[0m
[30;1m215 | [0m[35m    // If the value of the pointer is not the one of the node[0m
[30;1m216 | [0m[35m    // then we return the previous one[0m
[30;1m217 | [0m[35m    if (node == std::end(m_pointerMap)) {[0m

[30;1m247 | [0m[35m### Controlling When Expression are Evaluated[0m
[30;1m248 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m249 | [0m[35mThere are several ways to control when expressions are evaluated:[0m
[30;1m250 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m71 | [0m[35m\section TopicTemplateKeywordExplanation Explanation[0m
[30;1m72 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m73 | [0m[35mThe reason that the \c template keyword is necessary in the last example has to do with the rules fo[0m
[30;1m74 | [0m[35mtemplates are supposed to be compiled in C++. The compiler has to check the code for correct syntax [0m
[30;1m75 | [0m[35mpoint where the template is defined, without knowing the actual value of the template arguments (\c [0m
[30;1m76 | [0m[35mand \c Derived2 in the example). That means that the compiler cannot know that <tt>dst.triangularVie[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35ma member template and that the following &lt; symbol is part of the delimiter for the template[0m

[30;1m21 | [0m[35m  * This module provides SVD decomposition for matrices (both real and complex).[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m  * Two decomposition algorithms are provided:[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m  *  - JacobiSVD implementing two-sided Jacobi iterations is numerically very accurate, fast for sma[0m

[30;1m25 | [0m[35m  * These decompositions are accessible via the respective classes and following MatrixBase methods:[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m  *  - MatrixBase::jacobiSvd()[0m
[30;1m27 | [0m[35m  *  - MatrixBase::bdcSvd()[0m

[30;1m11 | [0m[35m\section TutorialAdvancedInitializationCommaInitializer The comma initializer[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35mEigen offers a comma initializer syntax which allows the user to easily set all the coefficients of [0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mvector or array. Simply list the coefficients, starting at the top-left corner and moving from left [0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mand from the top to the bottom. The size of the object needs to be specified beforehand. If you list[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mor too many coefficients, Eigen will complain.[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35m[0m
